'''Makenzie Jade Vega''' (born February 10, 1994) is an American [[Child actor|teen actress]].
==Personal life== Vega was born in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] to a [[Colombia]]n father and an American mother.<ref name="notitalian">{{cite web | author=Alexa Vega | title=Alexa Forever Forums | work=RE: Questions for Miss Alexa Vega | url=http://www.foreveralexaonline.com/forums/viewtopic.php?t=307&postdays=0&postorder=asc&start=307#6548 | quote=My father's side is Colombian (bogota)... and I don't know why they said my mom was Italian. She's not. My family and I were trying to figure out what my mom was, but we can only go back to 5 generations and they were all from Florida. haha. so .. Floridian? ahhah... my moms last name is French though | date=2005-05-11 | accessdate=2006-08-20}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> She is the younger sister of actress [[Alexa Vega]]. Vega currently lives in [[New York]] with her mother Gina Rue (a model),<ref>[http://www.filmreference.com/film/84/Alexa-Vega.html Alexa Vega Biography (1988-)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and three siblings. Vega attends a private all-girls Catholic school, on the Upper East Side.
==Career== At the age of five, Vega appeared regularly as the smallest child of Teddie Cochran ([[Geena Davis]]) in ''[[The Geena Davis Show]]''. In 2000, she was cast as Annie, the Campbellsâ precocious daughter<ref>"Annie's not much of a violin player, but she tries real hard. She's a little precocious, but that's only because she says what's on her mind." [http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0218967/quotes imdb quotes]</ref> in ''[[The Family Man]]''. The following year, Vega was seen again playing Chloe in ''[[Made (2001 film)|Made]]'' which starred [[Vince Vaughn]], [[Jon Favreau]] and [[Famke Janssen]]. In 2004, she played [[List of Saw Characters#Diana Gordon|Diana Gordon]], daughter of Dr. Lawrence Gordon ([[Cary Elwes]]) and Alison Gordon ([[Monica Potter]]) in the horror film ''[[Saw (film)|Saw]]''. Her next movie was ''[[Sin City (film)|Sin City]]'', in which she played young [[Nancy Callahan]], alongside [[Bruce Willis]]. Vega then appeared in ''[[Just My Luck (2006 film)|Just My Luck]]'', starring [[Lindsay Lohan]], and also in the summer blockbuster ''[[X-Men: The Last Stand]]'' as the Prison Truck Little Girl, where she was one of the forms that the [[shapeshifter]] [[Mystique (comics)|Mystique]] took, as an unsuccessful ploy to fool the guards into letting her go. Currently, she plays Grace, the daughter of Alicia Florrick, portrayed by [[Julianna Margulies]], in the CBS drama ''[[The Good Wife (TV series)|The Good Wife]]''.
